<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="716" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1766.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase—Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-19"><hi rend="italic">May 19,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>This morning the minister for foreign affairs said he was retaining
                            foreign portfolio solely in order to have direct charge of relations
                            with the United States, and that in his manifesto to the Mexican people
                            he would speak of the great service I had been able, on account of our
                            personal friendship, to render in maintaining good relations between our
                            two countries.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>